.Dd March 27, 2014
.Dt CAP_SANDBOXED 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm cap_sandboxed
.Nd Check if in a capability mode sandbox
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/capsicum.h
.In stdbool.h
.Ft bool
.Fn cap_sandboxed "void"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Fn cap_sandboxed
returns
.Va true
if the process is in a capability mode sandbox or
.Va false
if it is not.
This function is a more handy alternative to the
.Xr cap_getmode 2
system call as it always succeeds, so there is no need for error checking.
If the support for capability mode is not compiled into the kernel,
.Fn cap_sandboxed
will always return
.Va false .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Function
.Fn cap_sandboxed
is always successful and will return either
.Va true
or
.Va false .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cap_enter 2 ,
.Xr capsicum 4
